Description:
Something To Smile About
A former dental surgery perfectly suited to medical professionals, this potential packed property supports a raft of options including conversion to a residence and developing the generous site of 557m2 (subject to council approval). An extended Californian Bungalow that has been optimised for use as a clinic, yet is versatile enough to suit various other purposes, it's zoned General Residential (GRZ1). Highlighting a reception area/office, waiting room, six consulting rooms and a sizeable two room laboratory, it's certainly big on space. Additional features include a kitchenette, sterilization room, store room, three powder rooms, ducted heating, air conditioning, front garden, outdoor sitting area, side driveway and car parking for multiple vehicles. Close to buses, trams, trains and Sydney Road, this is an opportunity to shape the future that you ought to see for yourself.
Insights: 37 O'Hea Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017.

Description:
Design for Comfort, Located for Lifestyle
This superbly located three-bedroom townhouse delivers an exceptional lifestyle. With a well-designed floorplan layout, all three bedrooms include built in robes and master with walk in robe/ ensuite and well-appointed central bathroom. The property features a spacious light filled open plan living domain with stainless steel appliances, stone bench top and glass sliders that open to a low maintenance courtyard for entertaining. Completing the package is split system heating/cooling, remote controlled double car garage with rear access and community pool. Neighbouring the picturesque Merri Creek parklands and only minutes from public transport, schools Coburg Lake and Sydney Road eateries. Perfect for young professionals, families, first home buyers and investors, you are sure to be impressed.

Description:
Californian Class in a Prized Location
This captivating period home, ideally situated in one of Coburg's premier pockets, is certain to make a lasting impression with its charming period details, quality enhancements and easy access to an array of lifestyle attractions. Beyond its gorgeous facade, the home's inviting interior comprises two bedrooms (with BIRs) plus study/3rd bedroom, stylish central bathroom and separate powder room, light-filled lounge, dining area and contemporary kitchen with stainless steel appliances. Heating and cooling throughout, attic storage, lead-light windows and polished floorboards all add to the appeal, as well as a sizeable backyard garden with bungalow/studio (also air-conditioned), handy storage shed and established perimeter trees for added privacy. Complete with front off-street parking, it's close to local buses and Nicholson Street trams, primary and secondary schools, Merri Creek trails and parkland, Sydney Road cafes, restaurants and Coburg's renowned shopping precinct. Quality, convenience and classic style - perfect! Agentt: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Contemporary Style and Perfect Park Views
In a quiet Coburg cul-de-sac directly opposite the wide open spaces of Campbell Reserve, this attractive two-storey home presents a terrific low-maintenance lifestyle or investment opportunity. Light-filled interior showcases three upstairs bedrooms (large master with park views) and two-way central bathroom. Downstairs: front lounge leading through to the open dining area and adjoining kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances. Other features of the home include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, alarm system, new carpets, robes in all bedrooms and excellent storage spaces throughout, laundry and second WC, plus a north-facing courtyard with extensive paving, secure carport and additional driveway parking space. Wonderfully secluded yet incredibly convenient, it's also walking distance to Merri Creek trails, Nicholson Street/Moreland Road trams, as well as easy access to local schools, cafes and shopping precincts. How good is this!

Light, bright and brilliantly located

One of only five, the home presents striking polished timber floors throughout with spacious open living flowing into a streamlined kitchen integrating functional design. Relax And Enjoy

Description:
Exceptional Space, Style And Situation
Defined by contemporary elegance and space, this stylishly appointed three bedroom, two bathroom residence delivers a remarkable family environment. Situated in a peaceful pocket, on approximately 581m2, its generous open plan layout begins with a welcoming entrance and spacious lounge preceding generously proportioned kitchen, dining and living spaces enjoying seamless access to alfresco entertaining zones and large backyard. Designed for entertaining, the kitchen is the hub of the home and features stainless steel Fisher and Paykel appliances, comprising 900mm gas cook top, range hood, electric wall oven and double drawer dishwasher, as well as stone island, quality cabinetry and abundant storage. A magnificent staircase introduces a sundrenched balcony, along with three delightful bedrooms, including two with built-in-robes. The master boasts private balcony, walk-in-robe and luxury spa ensuite. Highlighted by a modern bathroom, powder room, heating/cooling, alarm, polished floorboards, plantation shutters and automated double garage with direct home entry. Sensationally located near vibrant cafes, shops, schools, Coburg Lake parklands and public transport.

Description:
Inspired Living In The Heart Of Coburg
Industrial edginess and contemporary style are showcased throughout this spacious two bedroom, two bathroom residence creating ambient indoor/outdoor areas enveloped in a unique historic setting. Situated within the former Pentridge workshop, the property comes with privileges such as private road access and individual courtyard entrance. Highlighted by exposed brickwork, timber beams and high ceilings, perfectly formed living, dining spaces accompany a smart kitchen zone flowing seamlessly onto a decked courtyard featuring custom-built seating, sub-deck storage and bluestone wall backdrop. Stylishly appointed with Caesarstone counters/waterfall island bench, Fisher and Paykel stainless steel appliances and pull out pantry, the two tone kitchen is both practical and easy on the eye. Upstairs finds two architecturally inspired bedrooms, including large main with abundant storage and modern ensuite. A main bathroom services the secondary bedroom which has built-in-robe. Features polished floorboards, skylights, split-systems, European laundry, alarm and car space. Excitingly close to vibrant cafes, continental shops, artisan markets, scenic Coburg Lake, cycle paths, schools and public transport.

Description:
Extended Elegance and Inner-Urban Ease
A captivating mix of classic and contemporary, this Californian Bungalow presents a lifestyle of impressive quality and indoor/outdoor family versatility in a sought-after pocket with the best of Coburg at your fingertips. Feature-packed and perfectly-presented, the home's inviting interior comprises three main bedrooms (master with BIR and stylish ensuite), home office/fourth bedroom, modern family bathroom and guest powder room (third WC). Dual living zones include a central lounge and light-filled open-plan living/dining area complemented by a well-appointed kitchen with Smeg/Bosch appliances and ample cupboard space. Add to this ducted heating and refrigerated cooling, high ceilings and polished floorboards (Sydney Blue Gum), integrated audio, solar power, large laundry and enormous fully-lined attic storeroom. Bi-folds from the living area (with retractable flywire screens) reveal an al-fresco style entertaining deck and undercover outdoor spa, plus north-facing backyard with established gardens, BBQ area and handy storage shed. Complete with two-car front off-street parking, it offers easy access to popular primary schools (St Fidelis and Coburg West), renowned shopping centre and Sydney Road cafes, as well as trains and trams to the CBD. Nothing to do but move in and start living!

Description:
Dual Frontage In Coburg's Prime Pocket
Explore the sensational possibilities presented by this original single bedroom home positioned on a coveted dual frontage block of approximately 337m2 in one of Coburg's premier locations.
Perched on Brunswick's fringe, in an area renowned for its community spirit, it is sure to appeal to renovators and families keen to enjoy the excellent proximity to vibrant Sydney Road shopping, cafes and trams, quality schools, Moreland Station, Upfield Bike Path and Nicholson Street trams, together with Merri Creek parklands and trails, all you desire is within easy reach.
In original condition, this classic home featuring expansive rooms with picture rails and decorative cornices, comprises a spacious entry hall, generous double bedroom with his and hers built-in robes, extensive living room with corner gas heater and a spacious kitchen with meals area featuring original cabinetry.
A serviceable bathroom, separate laundry and sunroom give way to a deep rear garden incorporating a large single garage and workshop that opens directly to Moore Street.
Whether you chose to renovate or further maximise the potential by subdivision or redevelopment (STCA), a singular opportunity to create something special begins here.

Description:
Premier Lifestyle Adjacent Parklands
Cradled between Merri Creek and the bustling trams and cafes of Nicholson Street you will find this three bedroom townhouse awarding the ultimate urban lifestyle. Presenting its own street frontage this thoughtfully designed townhouse impresses with its free flowing floorplan and high end finishes. Enter spacious open plan living where polished hardwood floors add warmth to relaxed living and dining, showcasing a pristine kitchen boasting granite counters, stainless steel appliances including dishwasher and ample storage. Flowing via sliding doors to a low maintenance courtyard where brightly planted garden beds add vibrancy, it promises a sunny outdoor space to enjoy.
Three privately zoned bedrooms are serviced by a spotless family bathroom, with the master suite featuring walk-in robe and ensuite, another bedroom effortlessly incorporating a study nook while the comfort and convenience of split system heating and cooling, video security, solar panels and single garage with remote door meet all the modern requirements. With parklands, schools, transport and cafes but a moment away, coupled with easy access to vibrant Sydney Road, iconic Lygon Street, the hospital/university precincts and CBD, it promises exceptional urban living.
Christina Spiteri : 0497 858 108

Description:
Classic Style with Room to Move
Instantly appealing with its perennial elegance and long list of features, this period-style home delivers an inner-urban lifestyle of quality and convenience along with plenty of potential to further enhance and extend (STCA) in a prime location just north of Brunswick's border. Beyond its gorgeous facade complete with decked verandah, the home's pristine interior boasts a wide central hallway accessing three generous bedrooms (master with full-width robes) and updated bathroom, spacious lounge through to the dining area and stone-top kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and Bosch dishwasher. Add to this ducted heating and split-system a/c, high ceilings, laundry and second WC, undercover decking, plus an expansive north-facing backyard garden with storage shed and 2000L watertank. Complete with front off-street parking, its walking distance to Moreland Station, choice of tram lines, local schools, as well as Sydney Road shops, cafes and restaurants.
Land Size: 404sqm Approximately

Description:
Modern Beauty In Historic Surrounds
As the street name suggests, this polished single bedroom, two bathroom apartment takes its place within the historic Pentridge precinct, superbly placed just moments to beautiful Coburg Lake Reserve, eclectic Sydney Road shops and cafes, Upfield Bike Path, Merri Creek Trail and Coburg Train Station. Securely and swiftly accessed via elevator transit, savvy new buyers, astute investors and discerning downsizers will be pleasantly surprised by its spacious interior and clever design elements. The living area is open in configuration, well illuminated and boasts excellent entertaining credentials including a contemporary kitchen with stone counters and a full complement of appliances. A seamless transition to the adjoining, north facing alfresco terrace blurs the line between indoor and outdoor living. Covered for continuous use, it's completed with integrated cupboards and a relaxing day bed concealing storage and tempting hours of sundrenched relaxation. Uniquely indulgent, two full bathrooms include a chic ensuite with oversized shower and central combining laundry function. The bedroom is generously proportioned and incorporates mirrored built-in wardrobes and a dedicated study nook. Presenting perfectly in pristine condition and enhanced with additional sought after features of secure undercover parking, ample storage including cage plus split system air conditioning, inspection will leave you breathless.
Alexkarbon Real Estate Pty Ltd
122 Errol Street, North Melbourne VIC 3051
